Class Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.felix.astar.algorithm.Node

  • public class Node
extends java.lang.Object
    The Node class represents a node inside the grid of the Pathfinder class.

        private void calculatefCost()
        Calculates the f costs by adding up the g and h cost. Called whenever one of them is updated.

      • setgCost

        protected void setgCost(int gCost)
        Sets the g-costs of this node and recalculates the f costs if the new g-costs aren't equal to the old.
        Parameters:
        gCost - the new g-costs.

      • sethCost

        protected void sethCost(int hCost)
        Sets the h-costs of this node and recalculates the f costs if the new h-costs aren't equal to the old.
        Parameters:
        hCost - the new g-costs.

      • setNodeType

        protected void setNodeType(NodeType nodeType)
        Sets the type of this node and calls the INodeUpdateListener if it was set. This method is preventing the start and end node from getting the NodeType NodeType.OPEN or NodeType.CLOSED
        Parameters:
        nodeType - the new type of this node.

      • setListener

        public void setListener(INodeUpdateListener listener)
        Sets the INodeUpdateListener for this Node. There can only be one listener at a time, so old listeners are overwritten. See the INodeUpdateListener documentation for further explanation.
        Parameters:
        listener - the new listener for this node.
